There are 4 new methods in the abstract interface Table:

    int getReadRpcTimeout();
    void setReadRpcTimeout(int readRpcTimeout);
    int getWriteRpcTimeout();
    void setWriteRpcTimeout(int writeRpcTimeout);

Tephra won't build without changes that implement these.

@ankitsinghal Just one more question (https://github.com/apache/incubator-tephra/pull/67#discussion_r169503415). 

Also the Java 7 build is failing for HBase 2.0 compat module. Looks like HBase 2.0 needs Java 8. Can you update the pom for the 2.0 compat module to use Java 8? 

Note that the master branch has some changes on how the Travis tests are run (TEPHRA-282). You'll have to rebase, and then add an entry to travis.yml for the 2.0 compat module.
